imports.value: DisplayAnnotationPart, DisplayAnnotationType, DisplayLine, DisplayList, DisplayMark, DisplayTextStyle, Annotation, DisplayMarkType, DisplayTextFragment, DisplaySourceLine, DisplayRawLine, DisplayHeaderType

defs.docs: A library for formatting of text or programming code snippets.

defs.name: display_list
defs.docs: display_list module stores the output model for the snippet.

defs.name: DisplayList
defs.docs: List of lines to be displayed.

defs.name: Annotation
defs.docs: Inline annotation which can be used in either Raw or Source line.

defs.name: Source
defs.docs: A line with `lineno` portion of the slice.

defs.name: Fold
defs.docs: A line indicating a folded part of the slice.

defs.name: Raw
defs.docs: A line which is displayed outside of slices.

defs.name: DisplayLine
defs.docs: A single line used in `DisplayList`.

defs.name: Content
defs.docs: A line with the content of the Slice.

defs.name: Annotation
defs.docs: An annotation line which is displayed in context of the slice.

defs.name: Empty
defs.docs: An empty source line.

defs.name: DisplaySourceLine
defs.docs: A source line.

defs.name: Origin
defs.docs:
A line which provides information about the location of the given
 slice in the project structure.

defs.name: Annotation
defs.docs: An annotation line which is not part of any snippet.

defs.name: DisplayRawLine
defs.docs:
Raw line - a line which does not have the `lineno` part and is not considered
 a part of the snippet.

defs.name: DisplayTextFragment
defs.docs: An inline text fragment which any label is composed of.

defs.name: DisplayTextStyle
defs.docs: A style for the `DisplayTextFragment` which can be visually formatted.

defs.name: Standalone
defs.docs: A standalone, single-line annotation.

defs.name: LabelContinuation
defs.docs: A continuation of a multi-line label of an annotation.

defs.name: Consequitive
defs.docs: A consequitive annotation in case multiple annotations annotate a single line.

defs.name: MultilineStart
defs.docs: A line starting a multiline annotation.

defs.name: MultilineEnd
defs.docs: A line ending a multiline annotation.

defs.name: DisplayAnnotationPart
defs.docs: An indicator of what part of the annotation a given `Annotation` is.

defs.name: DisplayMark
defs.docs: A visual mark used in `inline_marks` field of the `DisplaySourceLine`.

defs.name: AnnotationThrough
defs.docs: A mark indicating a multiline annotation going through the current line.

defs.name: AnnotationStart
defs.docs: A mark indicating a multiline annotation starting on the given line.

defs.name: DisplayMarkType
defs.docs: A type of the `DisplayMark`.

defs.name: DisplayAnnotationType
defs.value: DisplayAnnotationType::{None, Error, Warning, Info, Note, Help}
defs.docs: A type of the `Annotation` which may impact the sigils, style or text displayed.

defs.name: Initial
defs.docs: Initial header is the first header in the snippet.

defs.name: Continuation
defs.docs: Continuation marks all headers of following slices in the snippet.

defs.name: DisplayHeaderType
defs.docs:
Information whether the header is the initial one or a consequitive one
 for multi-slice cases.

defs.name: formatter
defs.docs:
DisplayListFormatter is a module handling the formatting of a
 `DisplayList` into a formatted string.

defs.name: style
defs.docs:
Set of structures required to implement a stylesheet for
 [DisplayListFormatter](super::DisplayListFormatter).

defs.name: Error
defs.docs: Message indicating an error.

defs.name: Warning
defs.docs: Message indicating a warning.

defs.name: Info
defs.docs: Message indicating an information.

defs.name: Note
defs.docs: Message indicating a note.

defs.name: Help
defs.docs: Message indicating a help.

defs.name: LineNo
defs.docs: Style for line numbers.

defs.name: Emphasis
defs.docs: Parts of the text that are to be emphasised.

defs.name: None
defs.docs: Parts of the text that are regular. Usually a no-op.

defs.name: StyleClass
defs.value: StyleClass::{Error, Warning, Info, Note, Help, LineNo, Emphasis, None}
defs.docs:
StyleClass is a collection of named variants of style classes
 that DisplayListFormatter uses.

defs.name: Style
defs.docs: This trait implements a return value for the `Stylesheet::get_style`.

defs.name: paint
defs.docs: The method used by the DisplayListFormatter to style the message.

defs.name: bold
defs.docs:
The method used by the DisplayListFormatter to display the message
 in bold font.

defs.name: Stylesheet
defs.docs:
Trait to annotate structs that can provide `Style` implementations for
 every `StyleClass` variant.

defs.name: get_style
defs.docs: Returns a `Style` implementer based on the requested `StyleClass` variant.

defs.name: DisplayListFormatter
defs.docs:
DisplayListFormatter' constructor accepts a single argument which
 allows the formatter to optionally apply colors and emphasis
 using `ansi_term` crate.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Constructor for the struct. The argument `color` selects
 the stylesheet depending on the user preferences and `ansi_term`
 crate availability.

defs.name: format
defs.docs: Formats a `DisplayList` into a String.

defs.name: snippet
defs.docs: Structures used as an input for the library.

defs.name: Snippet
defs.docs: Primary structure provided for formatting

defs.name: Slice
defs.value: Slice { source, line_start, origin, annotations, fold }
defs.docs:
Structure containing the slice of text to be annotated and
 basic information about the location of the slice.

defs.name: fold
defs.docs:
If set explicitly to `true`, the snippet will fold
 parts of the slice that don't contain any annotations.

defs.name: Error
defs.docs: Error annotations are displayed using red color and "^" character.

defs.name: Warning
defs.docs: Warning annotations are displayed using blue color and "-" character.

defs.name: AnnotationType
defs.docs: Types of annotations.

defs.name: SourceAnnotation
defs.docs: An annotation for a `Slice`.

defs.name: Annotation
defs.docs: An annotation for a `Snippet`.

defs.name: id
defs.docs: Identifier of the annotation. Usually error code like "E0308".

defs.name: stylesheets
defs.docs: List of stylesheets that can be used by the `DisplayListFormatter`.
